# Get User Tasks

The API endpoint retrieves the tasks associated with a specific user identified by the "identifier". The response is in JSON format and has a status code of 200.

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "tasks": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "_id": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "product": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "status": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "payrollDataAvailable": {
                "type": "boolean"
              },
              "createdAt": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "authenticated": {
                "type": "boolean"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

# Put User details

This endpoint allows you to update user information via an HTTP PUT request to {{apiUrl}}/user.

### Request Body

The request should include a JSON payload with the following structure:

``` json
{
    "identifier": "{{identifier}}",
    "data": {
        "account": {
            "accountNumber": "220000000",
            "routingNumber": "110000000",
            "type": "checking",
            "title": "Premier Plus Checking"
        }
    }
}

 ```

### Response

The response to this request will be in the form of a JSON schema with a status code of 200 and a content type of `application/json`. The response schema will be:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "success": {
            "type": "boolean"
        }
    }
}

 ```

# Get API Secrets

The `GET` request to `/secrets` endpoint retrieves a JSON response containing an array of `secrets` objects. Each `secrets` object includes the following properties:

- `_id` (string): The unique identifier for the secret.

- `createdAt` (string): The timestamp indicating when the secret was created.

- `endpoints` (array): An array of endpoint objects, each containing the following properties:

    - `_id` (string): The unique identifier for the endpoint.

    - `url` (string): The URL of the endpoint.

    - `eventTypes` (array): An array of event types associated with the endpoint.


Here is the JSON schema for the response:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "secrets": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "_id": { "type": "string" },
              "createdAt": { "type": "string" },
              "endpoints": {
                "type": "array",
                "items": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "_id": { "type": "string" },
                    "url": { "type": "string" },
                    "eventTypes": {
                      "type": "array",
                      "items": { "type": "string" }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
}

 ```

# Create API Secret

This endpoint allows you to create a new secret by sending an HTTP POST request to {{apiUrl}}/secrets. The request should include a raw payload in the request body with the name of the secret.

### Request Body

- name (string, required): The name of the secret.


#### Example

``` json
{
    "name": "treys secret"
}

 ```

### Response

Upon a successful request, the server will respond with a status code of 200 and a JSON object containing the newly created secret's data. The response will include the secret's ID, creation timestamp, name, and a token.

#### Example Response

``` json
{
    "data": {
        "secret": {
            "_id": "",
            "createdAt": "",
            "name": "",
            "token": ""
        }
    }
}

 ```

# Delete Secret

This endpoint is used to delete a specific secret identified by the `secretId`.

#### Request

- Method: DELETE

- URL: `{{apiUrl}}/secrets/:secretId`


#### Response

- Status: 200

- Content-Type: application/json

- { "success": true }


#### Request Body

This request does not require a request body.

#### Response Schema

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "success": {
            "type": "boolean"
        }
    },
    "required": ["success"]
}

 ```

# Post Webhooks Endpoint

This endpoint is used to create a new webhook endpoint.

#### Request

- Method: POST

- URL: {{apiUrl}}/webhooks/endpoints

- Body:

    - `url` (text): The URL to which the webhook events will be sent.

    - `secretId` (text): A unique identifier to authenticate the webhook events.

    - `eventTypes` (array): An array of event types for which the webhook should listen.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format and follows the schema below:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "endpoint": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "url": {
              "type": "string"
            },
            "secretId": {
              "type": "string"
            },
            "eventTypes": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "string"
              }
            },
            "_id": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

# Get Webhook Endpoints

This endpoint is used to create a get all webhook endpoint in the associated environment and customer instance.

#### Request

- Method: GET

- URL: {{apiUrl}}/webhooks/endpoints


Here's a JSON schema representing the response:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "endpoints": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "url": { "type": "string" },
              "secretId": { "type": "string" },
              "eventTypes": {
                "type": "array",
                "items": { "type": "string" }
              },
              "_id": { "type": "string" }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

# Update Webhook Endpoint

This endpoint allows you to update a specific webhook endpoint by providing the endpoint ID.

#### Request

- Method: PUT

- Endpoint: {{apiUrl}}/webhooks/endpoints/:endpointId


##### Request Body

- Type: Raw (application/json)

    - `url`: The URL of the webhook endpoint

    - `secretId`: The secret ID for the webhook endpoint

    - `eventTypes`: An array of event types to subscribe to


#### Response

The response is in JSON format and follows the schema below:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "endpoint": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "url": { "type": "string" },
            "secretId": { "type": "string" },
            "eventTypes": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": { "type": "string" }
            },
            "_id": { "type": "string" }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```
